com.randallscharpf.java.jmorsecoding.base.symbolsets

Class ExtendedInternationalSymbolSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.randallscharpf.java.jmorsecoding.base.symbolsets.SymbolSetBase
      • com.randallscharpf.java.jmorsecoding.base.symbolsets.ExtendedInternationalSymbolSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MorseSymbolSet

    public final class ExtendedInternationalSymbolSet
extends SymbolSetBase
    A symbol set that attempts to be able to convert any valid Unicode string to the Morse code sequence that corresponds to that string according to general consensus. General consensus is not a formal standard, but it can be a goal nonetheless, and so it is the goal of this implementation. Some characters and prosigns, therefore, may be misinterpreted by some in their Morse translations, but this is considered a superior choice to the choice of no translation at all.
    Since:
    1.0

    • Method Detail

      • getSymbolEnumClass

        protected java.lang.Class<? extends java.lang.Enum<? extends SymbolSetBase.MorseSymbol>> getSymbolEnumClass()
        Gives the class of an enumeration containing all the symbols that can be translated by this set. Includes all translatable prosigns and characters. The enumeration class must implement the SymbolSetBase.MorseSymbol interface.
        Implementing this method associates the implementations in this class (SymbolSetBase) with the data in the subclass while allowing subclasses to package their data in the form of an enumeration: the implicit superclass of Java's enumerations prevents the subclass itself from holding the data in this way. This method is not intended to be used outside of this class (SymbolSetBase).
        Specified by:
        getSymbolEnumClass in class SymbolSetBase

        the enum of symbols that this set supports translating
